5. AI MODEL USAGE RESTRICTIONS
   
   Google Gemini API:
   - Subject to Google's Generative AI Terms of Service
   - API key required (obtain from Google AI Studio)
   - Rate limits and quotas apply
   - Commercial use permitted per Google's terms
   
   Meta Platform APIs (WhatsApp/Instagram/Facebook):
   - Subject to Meta Platform Terms and Policies
   - Business verification may be required
   - API access requires Meta App approval
   - Privacy policy compliance mandatory
   
   Local AI Models (Ollama/GGUF):
   - Subject to individual model licenses
   - Some models restrict commercial use
   - Check model card before deployment

6. DATA PRIVACY AND SECURITY
   
   GDPR/KVKK Compliance:
   - User consent required for data processing
   - Right to access, modify, and delete data
   - Data retention policies must be implemented
   - Cross-border data transfer restrictions apply
   
   Face Recognition Data:
   - Biometric data must be encrypted at rest
   - Secure storage and transmission required
   - User consent mandatory before capture
   - Data deletion upon request
   
   Conversation Logs:
   - End-to-end encryption recommended
   - Secure storage implementation required
   - Retention period must be defined
   - Access controls must be enforced

7. SECURITY REQUIREMENTS
   
   Production Deployment:
   - Security audit recommended before deployment
   - HTTPS/TLS encryption mandatory
   - Regular security updates required
   - Vulnerability disclosure policy recommended
   
   API Keys and Secrets:
   - Never commit API keys to version control
   - Use environment variables for secrets
   - Rotate keys regularly
   - Implement key management system

8. PROHIBITED USES
   
   You may NOT use this software for:
   - Illegal activities or purposes
   - Violating privacy rights
   - Harassment or discrimination
